data.event: The early Malay place name of Changi was Tanjong Rusa, which is found in the 1604 E.G. de Eredia map of Singapore.

event.title: 1828 map by Franklin and Jackson, the extreme southeastern tip of the island is referred

data.event: In the 1828 map by Franklin and Jackson, the extreme southeastern tip of the island is referred to as Tanjong Changi.

event.title: days of the sixteenth century Johor kingdom located

data.event: The local name Changi must have been a significant point for the Malays, especially in the days of the sixteenth century Johor kingdom located on the Johor River.
